OK, here we go. My ftp host address is ftp.purpleocity.net. My user name is claresudbery@purpleocity.net. The url of all stuff I upload is www.claresudbery.purpleocity.net/[filename]. So the url is www.[first part of username].[ftp host address minus the "ftp" bit]

What do you reckon? Does that look familiar? Can you convert that into how your system works?

I honestly don't think you have to create pages on your ftp server (but I am generalising our from my own specific experience, which is hardly scientific). But you may want to create directories to store your bits and bobs in. FTP Explorer will allow you to do that.

