P.S. You know the way you linked to Boob Pencil and then told people to scroll down and find a post called 'blblblbl'? No need to do that.

In Blogger, at the bottom of each post you'll find the time of the post. If you right-click on the time and choose 'Properties' you'll find it is in fact a link to that post, so you can grab the url and use it as a way of linking to a specific post. That way you can link from your post to someone else's post (or indeed one of your own) and the link will always be valid; will always take readers to that specific post, rather than just linking to the blog containing it.

